section.section:
A person who is convicted under subsection (a) of this section or of conspiracy to commit a crime included in subsection (a) of this section shall be sentenced to imprisonment for not less than 40 years and is subject to a fine not exceeding $100,000 if the person previously has served three or more separate terms of confinement as a result of three or more separate convictions:
under subsection (a) of this section or § 5-609 of this subtitle;
of conspiracy to commit a crime included in subsection (a) of this section or § 5-609 of this subtitle;
of a crime under the laws of another state or the United States that would be a crime included in subsection (a) of this section or § 5-609 of this subtitle if committed in this State; or
of any combination of these crimes.
